Shanghai serial killer sentenced to death . A man charged with a series of killings and robberies against women that shook Shanghai earlier this year was sentenced to death on Thursday by a local court , the Xinmin Evening News reported . The court heard that Wei Guangxiu carried out 13 attacks on women using an iron bar between March 18 and April 14 , and two women were killed and 12 injured , the newspaper said . The motive for the attacks was robbery . It did not say anything about a possible appeal or when the sentence would be carried out . The case caused a spate of lurid rumours in the city prior to Wei ' s capture due to a complete lack of information in the official media on the case . 
